sql:
SELECT AVG(comment_count) AS average_comments_per_project
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(comment_id) AS comment_count
  FROM comments
  GROUP BY project_id
) AS subquery;

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed more than once" refers to projects that have more than one record in the `projects` table;
- "status" refers to the current status of the project (e.g., Completed, Accepted);
- "total number of comments" refers to the sum of comments received for all projects with the same status.

sql:
SELECT title
FROM projects
WHERE milestone_count = (SELECT MAX(milestone_count) FROM projects);

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_project_count
FROM projects
WHERE status = 'Completed' AND priority IN ('High', 'Medium');
